  <front>
   <head>An Epitaph on the late Lord Mount-Cashel.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">are snatch'd away sometimes,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To punish Parents for their Crimes.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thy Mother's Merit was so great,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Heav'n hasten'd thy untimely Fate,</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To make her Character complete.</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tho' many Virtues fill'd her Breast,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Twas  crown'd the rest.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
